				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Question about Amplification<a name="17799"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 29 04 12:28 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Amp is useful on all voice oriented songs.  Duh, I know.  But what I mean is, if you REALLY need the benefits from a voice song or songs during a twist, and have a gem open, it doesn't hurt to twist it in.  That and at 5 ticks, you can do it with 3 other songs fairly easily with few drops.  
<br />

<br />
My best example of using AMP would be if you were a mid 30s or 40s bard in a group (LDoN is a good example) and your cleric was LOM and you were behind schedule.  32 manasong is voice, so AMP takes it from 7 mana a tick to 12 I think.  It can make downtimes (or buffing times) significantly shorter.  
<br />

<br />
Another example is if you really need a high damage shield, most DS's are voice so you can nearly double the DS output if you twist that in.  
<br />

<br />
I'm sure if you study the songlist and Reeds for the impacts of AMP on songs, that you will soon see many more examples of how nice this song can be.  It's not an everyday song, but it has its uses.
<br />

<br />
Sinfonian</span></td>
