				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Question about Amplification<a name="17814"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 29 04 1:16 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Amp also helps for our haste + buff and slow + debuff songs (verses of victory and Largos 51 come to mind).  While it wont affect the amount of haste or slow it will amp the stats and often it is quite significant.
<br />

<br />
One twist I will use if I am the slower and haster is
<br />

<br />
Battle cry
<br />
Amp
<br />
LAB (51 Largos)
<br />
VoV
<br />
Psalm (usually disease)
<br />
If I miss a note (or two - does anyone else get missed notes in multiples?) I just skip the DS.
<br />

<br />
This will give:
<br />
54 Str &amp; Agi and 37 AC (from VOV)
<br />
Debuff the mob for -82 AGI and -28 AC (From Largos)
<br />
16 DS and 9 ac from Psalm
<br />
30% haste and 15% overhaste.
<br />
32% slow and snare the mob.
<br />

<br />
It makes quite an impact.</span></td>
