			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Question about Amplification<a name="17983"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 30 04 10:02 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>There's quite a few great uses for amp, but as usual, it all depends on the group make-up and your own personal judgement. I'll give a few examples of when I would use Amp but I am no expert so please keep this in mind. 
<br />
    I have a few different song setups, one is called Primary Haste-Slow. This is for when there is no slower or haster in the group, I always ask to pull, simply put because I don't trust anyone else and I'm not going to die again in LDoN because I was too nice to put my foot down. When I am primary haster/slower it goes like this. 
<br />

<br />
1. Amp
<br />
2. Slow
<br />
3. Verses 
<br />
4. Katta's or Battlecry (depending on grp makeup)
<br />
5. lull 
<br />
6. song of twilight
<br />
7. song of dawn
<br />
8. Chorus of clarity
<br />

<br />
My second set is called (you guessed it) Secondary Haste/Slow. This is for when I have a nice chanty or shammy in the group and my line-up is as follows:
<br />

<br />
1. Battle Cry
<br />
2. Katta's
<br />
3. Verses
<br />
4. Chorus of clarity (or Rizlona's fire)
<br />
5. Lull 
<br />
6. Song of twilight
<br />
7. Song of Dawn
<br />
8. Niv's Melody
<br />

<br />
   You may notice I don't have amp in there. I switch things up depending on whether the haste/slow is a chanter or a shammy. If there's a chanter in the group I can talk to them and remove my mez (song of twilight). If that's the case it goes like this:
<br />

<br />
1. Amp 
<br />
2. Verses
<br />
3. Battlecry 
<br />
4. Katta's
<br />
5. Damage Shield
<br />
6. Lull
<br />
7. Song of Dawn
<br />
8. Niv's
<br />

<br />
   My preference is to pull with song of Dawn after lulls so I always try and keep my hotkeys setup the same. With this setup you can see that my lull and pull songs have moved, I have a special bank setup to relay the same hotkey positions for this lineup, I just switch banks so I can utilize the eztra slot opened from not using mezz. In my very humble opinion, Amp is best utilized to boost the Haste line with stats (GREAT boost) and/or the DS line. Keep your eyes open, it's your job to not only know your role, but the roles of all the others in your group so you can make them better! I also substitute Rizlona's and the Rune line we have a lot too, again it all depends on the group make-up and I'm only lvl 54 right now so I'm sure there will be plenty more shuffling of songs to come. 
<br />

<br />

<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
